media.headline: Strasburg's first pitch

media.bigblurb: Stephen Strasburg tosses his first pitch of the 2017 season to Dee Gordon at Nationals Park

media.headline: Strasburg fans Yelich
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Strasburg retires Yelich with a strikeout
media.bigblurb: Stephen Strasburg finishes off a 1-2-3 1st inning by striking out Christian Yelich, his first of the 2017 season

media.headline: Volquez strikes out Harper
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Volquez sits down Harper with a K
media.bigblurb: Edinson Volquez records his first strikeout of the 2017 season as he gets Bryce Harper to go down swinging in the bottom of the 1st

media.headline: Army Brass performs anthem
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: U.S. Army Brass Quintet performs anthem
media.bigblurb: The U.S. Army Brass Quintet performs the national anthem before the Nationals host the Marlins on Opening Day in Washington. D.C.

media.headline: Stanton drives in Realmuto
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Stanton crushes an RBI double to center
media.bigblurb: Giancarlo Stanton brings in the first run of 2017 for the Marlins as he launches a double to center to bring home J.T. Realmuto

media.headline: Service members' first pitch
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: U.S. service members throw first pitch
media.bigblurb: U.S. Armed Forces service members throw out the ceremonial first pitch before the Nationals host the Marlins on Opening Day

media.headline: Ozuna's RBI single
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Ozuna rips an RBI single back up the middle
media.bigblurb: Marcell Ozuna jumps on a 1-0 pitch and lines it back up the middle to bring in Giancarlo Stanton and double the Marlins' lead to 2-0

media.headline: Nationals' starting lineup
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Nationals's lineup introduced on Opening Day
media.bigblurb: The Nationals open the 2017 season at home against the Marlins and the starting lineup is announced in front of a packed stadium

media.headline: Turner's impressive stop
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Turner nabs Hechavarria with diving stop
media.bigblurb: Adeiny Hechavarria hits a hard grounder to the left side and Trea Turner lays out to make a terrific stop to start a 6-3 putout in the 5th

media.headline: Harper's leaping catch
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Harper pulls down nice grab on warning track
media.bigblurb: Bryce Harper tracks Christian Yelich's deep fly ball to the warning track and makes a terrific leaping catch before hitting the wall

media.headline: Harper belts first HR of season
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Harper crushes a solo homer to right
media.bigblurb: Bryce Harper puts the Nationals on the board in the 6th as he launches the ball over the wall in right for his first home run of 2017

media.headline: Lind's go-ahead pinch-hit HR
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Lind jacks a two-run homer to right
media.bigblurb: Adam Lind makes his first appearance as a National and launches a pinch-hit, two-run homer to right, giving his team a 3-2 lead in the 7th

media.headline: Gordon, Marlins honor Fernandez
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Gordon's special Jose Fernandez shoe insoles
media.bigblurb: Dee Gordon gets a surprise with custom-made Jose Fernandez inspired shoe insoles and the rest of the team wears a commemorative patch

media.headline: Werth's warning-track grab
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Werth leaps to make nifty grab in deep left
media.bigblurb: Giancarlo Stanton hits a deep fly ball to left and Jayson Werth tracks it to the warning track and makes a nice catch

media.headline: Statcast: Harper's solo homer
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Statcast measures Harper's 419-foot homer
media.bigblurb: Statcast measures the exit velocity, launch angle and projected distance of Bryce Harper's solo home run

media.headline: Statcast: Stanton's RBI double
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Statcast measures Stanton's RBI double
media.bigblurb: Statcast measures the exit velocity and projected distance of Giancarlo Stanton's RBI double

media.headline: Treinen shuts the door
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Treinen fans Ozuna to pick up the save
media.bigblurb: Blake Treinen puts the finishing touches on a 4-2 win for the Nationals by getting Marcell Ozuna to go down swinging in the top of the 9th

media.headline: Murphy's RBI single
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Murphy brings in Eaton with a single
media.bigblurb: Daniel Murphy clubs a single into right field and Adam Eaton comes in to score, doubling the Nationals' lead to 4-2 in the bottom of the 8th

media.headline: Statcast: Lind's two-run HR
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Statcast measures Lind's 415-ft home run
media.bigblurb: Statcast measures the exit velocity, launch angle and projected distance of Adam Lind's go-ahead two-run home run

media.headline: Yelich's diving grab
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Yelich lays out to take a hit from Turner
media.bigblurb: Christian Yelich charges in and lays out to make a terrific catch that takes a hit away from Trea Turner in the bottom of the 5th

media.headline: Baker on Opening Day win
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Baker on Nationals' first win of 2017 season
media.bigblurb: Nationals manager Dusty Baker talks about the team's overall production in a 4-2 Opening Day win over the Marlins

media.headline: Mattingly on Opening Day loss
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Mattingly on pitching in loss to Nationals
media.bigblurb: Marlins manager Don Mattingly talks about the 4-2 loss to the Nationals, the pitching by Edinson Volquez, and the struggles in the bullpen

media.headline: Phelps retires Zimmerman
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Phelps sits down Zimmerman in the 6th
media.bigblurb: David Phelps collects one of his two strikeouts in two innings of work as he gets Ryan Zimmerman to go down looking to end the 6th inning

media.headline: Must C: Lind homers, celebrates
media.blurb: Must C Curtains: Lind amped after pinch-hit homer
media.bigblurb: Adam Lind hits a pinch-hit, go-ahead home run in the 7th inning and celebrates during his trip around the bases, then takes a curtain call

media.headline: Lind on his go-ahead homer
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Lind on his pinch-hit go-ahead home run
media.bigblurb: Adam Lind talks about his pinch-hit go-ahead home run in his first at-bat for the Nationals, leading them to a 4-2 win over the Marlins

media.headline: Baker mixes up Adam Lind's name
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Baker confuses Adam Lind with Jeremy Lin
media.bigblurb: Nationals manager Dusty Baker is talking about the clutch hitting of Adam Lind, but accidentally gets his name mixed up with another person

media.headline: Harper's strong Opening Day
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Harper's solid all-around Opening Day
media.bigblurb: Bryce Harper starts his 2017 season in style as he makes a sparkling catch in the 5th and then clubs a solo home run in the 6th

media.headline: Recap: MIA 2, WSH 4
media.blurb: 4/3/17: Lind, Harper lead Nats to Opening Day win
media.bigblurb: Daily Recap: Bryce Harper clubbed a solo home run in the 6th and Adam Lind belted a go-ahead, two-run homer in the 7th in a 4-2 win

media.headline: Strasburg's Opening Day start
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Strasburg throws seven in season debut
media.bigblurb: Stephen Strasburg allows two runs on six hits and collects three strikeouts in seven innings of work to earn the win vs. the Marlins

media.headline: Volquez's scoreless start
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Volquez fans six in Opening Day start
media.bigblurb: Edinson Volquez allows four hits and one walk while striking out six in five scoreless innings of work on Opening Day
